Crossbow, Repeating Heavy	KEY:Crossbow (Repeating Heavy)	PROFICIENCY:WEAPON|Crossbow (Repeating Heavy)	TYPE:Weapon.Container.Exotic.Ranged.Piercing.Standard.Container.Projectile.Crossbow											CONTAINS:UNLIM|Weapon Crystal=1	CONTAINS:UNLIM|Bolt|SpecificBolt			COST:400	WT:12							CRITMULT:x2	CRITRANGE:2							DAMAGE:1d10				EQMOD:WOOD													RANGE:120								SOURCEPAGE:p.116																																																			SPROP:The repeating crossbow (Whether heavy or light) holds 5 crossbow bolts. As long as it holds bolts, you can reload it by pulling the reloading lever (a free action). Loading a new case of 5 bolts is a full-round action that provokes attacks of opportunity. You can firea repeating crossbow with one hand or fire a repeating crossbow in each hand in the same manner as you would a normal crossbow of the same size. However, you must fire the weapon with two hands in order to use the reloading lever, and you must use two hands to load a new case of bolts.
