Hammer, Gnome Hooked		KEY:Hammer (Gnome Hooked)		PROFICIENCY:WEAPON|Hammer (Gnome Hooked)		TYPE:Weapon.Container.Melee.Exotic.Double.Standard.Gnome.Bludgeoning.Hammer					ALTTYPE:Weapon.Melee.Piercing			CONTAINS:UNLIM|Weapon Crystal=1									COST:20	WT:6							CRITMULT:x3	CRITRANGE:1	ALTCRITMULT:x4	ALTCRITRANGE:1	DAMAGE:1d8	ALTDAMAGE:1d6	EQMOD:STEEL			ALTEQMOD:STEEL	WIELD:TwoHanded												SIZE:M	SOURCEPAGE:p.118																																																			SPROP:A gnome hooked hammer is a double weapon. You can fight with it as if fighting with two weapons, but if you do, you incur all the normalattack penalities associated with fighting with two weapons, just as if you were using a one-handed weapon and a light weapon. The hammer's blunt head is a bludgeoning weapon that deals 1d6 points of damage (crit x3). Its hook is a peircing weapon that deals 1d4 points of damage (crit x4). You can use either head as the primary weapon. The other head is the off-hand weapon. A creature wielding a gnome hooked hammer in one hand can't use it as a double weapon - only one end of the weapon can be used in any given round. You can use the hook on a gnome hooked hammer to make tripattacks. If you are tripped during your own trip attempt, you can drop the gnome hooked hammer to avoid being tripped. Gnomes treat gnome hooked hammers as martial weapons.
